qx|A5a,When to Lead Trumps|HT|E|FP|1|cs|1|CP|4|at|^-
{        When to Lead Trumps        }
^-|CS|6|CP||fp||AT|^C@2^Y@3You should lead a trump when you have reason to believe dummy (or declarer) is short in one of their partner's suits, particularly if you are long in that suit. If declarer bids 2 suits, and dummy shows a preference, it is likely that dummy is short in the other of declarer's suits. On those sorts of auctions, a trump lead should be seriously considered. For example, assume the following auction:
^-
{|ia|1HP1SP2CP3CPPP|at|}

As North a club lead might very well be your best lead, particularly if you are long in hearts or spades. |
PG| ***** 47 ***** |


NT||
