AT|

Defense is the most difficult part of bridge. Even the experts make lots of defensive errors. What I hope to do here is give you a good grounding of the fundamentals of defense. You should not expect to play perfect defense but, if you learn the fundamentals, you will do much better on average than most of your peers.|
PG| ***** 164 ***** |


AT|

Opening leads in particular are very difficult. It is an important defensive tool, and can often make the difference between a contract making or being set. What I am going to do is give you guidelines for making good opening leads. If you follow these guidelines, you will do better than most. There are occasional hands where an unorthodox brilliant lead beats an otherwise unbeatable contract and there are many player who look for these brilliant leads, (and usually fail).|
PG| ***** 165 ***** |


AT|

My advice is to stick to the basics. If you execute the fundamentals better than your peers, you will do better in the long run.|
PG| ***** 166 ***** |


